      <dt>Rule 1</dt>
      <dd>The CTF event is open to anyone who wants to participate. All you need is an account at the platform.</dd>
      <dt>Rule 2</dt>
      <dd>Each team must have between three and five members.</dd>
      <dt>Rule 3</dt>
      <dd>
        The CTF will be "challenge based" i.e:
        <ul style="list-style: inside;">
          <li>The CTF is seperated into small tasks that will be solved individually.</li>
          <li>The Covered topics are somewhere around crypto, Web security, reverse engineering and Web forencics.</li>
        </ul>
      </dd>
      <dt>Rule 4</dt>
      <dd>Each task  must be solved using tools that are within the some field. Each task gives a set of points depending on the difficulty.
        The teams will be ranked based of their scores.</dd>
      <dt>Rule 5</dt>
      <dd>The winning team will be the one with the highest score. If two or more teams have the same score, an additional task will be given
        and the winner will be the quickest to solve it.</dd>
      <dt>Rule 6</dt>
      <dd>No Dos/automated scans, cyberattacks, deleting stuff on our servers.</dd>
      <dt>Rule 7</dt>
      <dd>If you break the rules we will kick you butt and remove all your points and your team will be excluded.</dd>
    </dl>
